commit_message:
`setup.py` improvements

+ find_packages instead of complicated comprehencion
+ only `setup` and `find_packages` imported from setuptools
Use common practice approaches with requirements and packaging
Add Python Highlighting to Python Code
Add Tox configuration, run Travis builds with Tox

When tracing 'call' events, skip lines containing decorators to print actual function name.

Python syntax expects function decorators in a separate line so the all lines starting with '@' can be safely skipped.
Test that actual function name (and not decorator) is reported for 'call' event.
Be safe and check that a function definition is found
Rework code to find a function definition in case of decorated source lines
Add test-case for multiline decorator and lambda
Remove --verbose, causes problems in Wing IDE
Refactor showing return values, repr, tests
Bump version, authors and edit readme
Fail gracefully when can't find code
Fix bug in not closing file on PyPy
Bundling decorator and six, look ma no dependencies!
Add links to some online media coverage.
Don't require setup.py to import pysnooper
Part 2: Don't require setup.py to import pysnooper
Remove need for conditional .decode() call which gives warning

Basic fixes for linters: remove unused variables and imports, plus whitespace and other style improvements for PEP8

Edited by Ram.

# Conflicts:
#	pysnooper/pysnooper.py
#	tests/test_pysnooper.py
Remove more calls to decode using u prefix
Make it easier to read assert_output failure by showing mismatched line rather than just mismatched length. Also, .format can't evaluate arbitrary Python
Fix incorrect tuple passed to variables in test
Use dedent for nice multiline string
Allow tracking arbitrary expressions in 'variables' using eval
reprlib already handles both truncation and exceptions

PR feedback:
Swap imports
Raise maxother locally
Demo long variable output
More informative repr for exceptions. Forgot to use repr_instance
IronPython doesn't always have frame.f_globals, fix #75
Catch ValueError because IronPython raises it on bad filename #75
Workaround for Unicode display on Py2.7, fix #67

Allow a callable to be passed to snoop()

Fixes: #80

Add classes to automatically track attributes, keys, etc. of variables

# Conflicts:
#	pysnooper/tracer.py
Enumerate is too risky - it exhausts iterators and will show changes when sets change order
Use collections ABCs to be safe
A weird __eq__ method could raise an exception when using 'in'
Test output directly to Path object (currently fails)
Test for open attribute on output, to support Paths
Only add parentheses to exploded expressions if needed

commit_message: add usage to package docstring; fixes #83
Make Tracer a class based decorator
Allow using snoop as context manager
Improve checks for tracing, add tests for with blocks
Optimisation: return None when not tracing frame to avoid line events
Cache source by both module name and filename. Fixes #101
Make generate_authors.py write binary to support Unicode
Remove `reprlib` because it's not reliable for simple cases
Keep proper track of previous tracing functions

Add support for thread identifiers

Display thread infos (identifier and name) on output to help
user to track execution on apps who use threading.
Delete frames when exiting to free up memory
Truncate long variables in the middle
Indent based on how many calls are currently being traced
Store depth globally to indent correctly in all cases
Add indentation tests with new assert_sample_output
Newest python versions have different repr for exceptions, avoid altogether

Preserve the local variables order in the output.

The variables are outputed in the declare order, instead of alphabetical.

This causes function arguments to be printed in the declare order.
All watched variables are outputted after declared ones.

Make predictable order of items if we don't know the proper order.

Also fix tests
Simplify the new and modified values reporting.
Restore cell vars support in the ordered printing.
Rewrite get_local_reprs to use sort explicitely
Make order test more reliable on pypy

Make frame_to_local_reprs a dict

Co-Authored-By: Alex Hall <alex.mojaki@gmail.com>
Move one string of code down in get_local_reprs
Don't always place new variables before the modified ones

Make vars_order line a bit shorter

Co-Authored-By: Alex Hall <alex.mojaki@gmail.com>
Handle overwriting in FileWriter instead of Tracer
move the type difference declaration to pycompat
Fix unicode issues and add test, fix #124
improve README, and test dependency numpy
support activate and deactivate snooper by environment variable and setup snooper global or in-scope
add unittest for activate and setup snoop
removing python_toolbox reference, not needed anymore
Show source path, especially when multiple files
Mention the option of decorating classes in the README.md
Add a test to demonstrate the suboptimal but noncatastrophic behaviour when used with properties
Move the class-tests to the right place chronologically
Add some more tests for the behaviour with decorators
Avoid snooping on the base class
Use .items() to get rid of a call to getattr
Use slightly more specific regexes in the tests
Update regexes in tests to work with Python 2.7
Add Jonathan Reichelt Gjertsen to authors
Bugfix: don't try to snoop on coroutines
Reject coroutine functions and async generator functions #152
Tests: Better time regex and placeholder

Force time.isoformat to show microseconds every time

Fix #158

Add test for decorating when DISABLED = True

Fix #154

Fix unit tests on thread_info

The length of thread's ident between "MainThread" and others are not
always equal. So use another way to check it.

Add normalize flag to remove machine-specific data

This allows for diffing between multiple PySnooper outputs.
